  3. Updated to_dict() to include entity_type - Serialization now includes the type discriminator.

  4. Refactored isinstance chain in context_first_mixin.py:701-717:

  # Before (isinstance chain)
  if isinstance(entity, ContextualKnowledge):
      knowledge_reqs.append(entity)
  elif isinstance(entity, ContextualTask):
      task_reqs.append(entity)
  elif isinstance(entity, ContextualHabit):
      habit_reqs.append(entity)

  # After (dictionary dispatch)
  type_categorizers: dict[str, list] = {
      "knowledge": knowledge_reqs,
      "task": task_reqs,
      "habit": habit_reqs,
  }

  for entity in enriched:
      if entity.entity_type in type_categorizers:
          type_categorizers[entity.entity_type].append(entity)

  Benefits

  1. Unified pattern - Both isinstance and string comparisons now use same source of truth
  2. Extensible - Adding new entity types requires only adding the property override
  3. Serialization-friendly - entity_type included in to_dict() output
  4. Match-ready - Enables Python 3.10+ pattern matching:
  match entity.entity_type:
      case "task": handle_task(entity)
      case "knowledge": handle_knowledge(entity)
  5. Aligns with existing code - ScheduleAwareRecommendation.entity_type already uses this pattern

